<h2>Multi-select Dropdown — the multiple-select droplist</h2>
<p>The <strong>multi-select dropdown</strong> is the <a href="/blocks/droplist/">droplist family</a> member for choosing <em>several</em> values from one button-triggered listbox. It is the <a href="/blocks/dropdown/">dropdown</a> with exactly one trait flipped — <code>selection</code> moves from <code>model=single</code> to <code>model=multiple;selectionFollowsFocus=false</code> — and nothing else. As a form-associated custom element it participates in <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> submission, <code>FormData</code>, reset, and validity exactly like the native <code>&lt;select multiple&gt;</code>, submitting one entry per selected value.</p>

<h3>Trait selection at a glance</h3>
<p>The multi-select dropdown's identity is fixed by these trait selections. The <strong>only</strong> difference from the dropdown is the <code>selection</code> row; the focus, anchor, and type-ahead picks are identical. Structural picks are <strong>local</strong> (an author cannot change them via props or ambient intent); behavioral picks are this component's <em>stance</em> and remain overridable by an ambient <code>droplistIntent</code>:</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Trait</th><th>Dimension</th><th>Value</th><th>Kind</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/selection/">Selection</a></td><td><code>model</code></td><td><code>multiple</code>, <code>selectionFollowsFocus=false</code></td><td><strong>structural</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/type-ahead/">Type-Ahead</a></td><td>presence</td><td>on (mutually exclusive with filter)</td><td><strong>structural</strong></td></tr>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/focus-delegation/">Focus Delegation</a></td><td><code>strategy</code></td><td><code>virtual</code> (<code>aria-activedescendant</code>)</td><td>behavioral</td></tr>
    <tr><td><a href="/intents/anchor/">Anchor</a></td><td>placement / collision</td><td><code>bottom-start</code> / <code>flip,resize</code></td><td>behavioral</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Altitude 1 — HTML, explicit behaviors (the substrate)</h3>
<p>The same substrate as the dropdown; only the <code>selection</code> attribute value changes, and the listbox carries <code>aria-multiselectable="true"</code>. <code>model=multiple</code> switches selection to the decoupled toggle model — Space toggles <code>aria-selected</code> on the focused option — and <code>selectionFollowsFocus=false</code> stops auto-commit, so the arrow keys move virtual focus only. The JSX mirror is near-identity — only the inline comments (<code>&lt;!-- --&gt;</code> → <code>{/* */}</code>) and the two-root wrapper (a <code>&lt;&gt;</code> fragment) differ:</p>
{{ sourceToggle("multi-substrate") }}
{% highlight "html" %}
<button aria-haspopup="listbox" anchor="tag-list"
        commandfor="tag-list" command="toggle-popover">Tags</button>

<ul id="tag-list" role="listbox" aria-multiselectable="true"
    focus-delegation="strategy=virtual"                       <!-- behavioral; may default from ambient intent -->
    selection="model=multiple;selectionFollowsFocus=false"    <!-- STRUCTURAL: always local -->
    type-ahead
    anchored="placement=bottom-start;collision=flip,resize"
    popover>
  <li role="option" composite-descendant data-value="design">Design</li>
  <li role="option" composite-descendant data-value="eng">Engineering</li>
</ul>
{% endhighlight %}
{{ jsxSource("multi-substrate") }}
{% highlight "tsx" %}
<>
  <button aria-haspopup="listbox" anchor="tag-list"
          commandfor="tag-list" command="toggle-popover">Tags</button>

  <ul id="tag-list" role="listbox" aria-multiselectable="true"
      focus-delegation="strategy=virtual"                       {/* behavioral; may default from ambient intent */}
      selection="model=multiple;selectionFollowsFocus=false"    {/* STRUCTURAL: always local */}
      type-ahead
      anchored="placement=bottom-start;collision=flip,resize"
      popover>
    <li role="option" composite-descendant data-value="design">Design</li>
